01:29.155 --> 01:30.789
I'm looking for...
I'm looking for Amy Fleming.

01:30.856 --> 01:32.291
Has she been admitted here?

01:32.325 --> 01:33.558
Are you a relative
of miss Fleming?

01:33.592 --> 01:34.992
Yes, I'm her fiance.

01:35.027 --> 01:36.694
Can you tell me where she is,
please?

01:36.729 --> 01:39.564
She's been admitted to the icu.

01:39.632 --> 01:40.932
To the icu?

01:40.966 --> 01:42.434
What happened?
Is she all right?

01:42.468 --> 01:43.535
Have a seat.

01:43.569 --> 01:45.069
I just need to see her
if that's okay.

01:45.103 --> 01:48.873
A doctor will be with you
shortly.

01:48.908 --> 01:50.308
Okay.

01:59.151 --> 02:01.785
Ty?! How is she?

02:01.820 --> 02:04.855
- You tell me. What the hell happened?
- I don't know.

02:04.889 --> 02:06.090
What do you mean
you don't know?

02:06.158 --> 02:08.258
- You were with her, weren't you?
- No, I wasn't.

02:08.292 --> 02:09.693
I heard the noise
of the horses,

02:09.727 --> 02:12.195
but by the time I got to
the stable, Amy was down.

02:12.229 --> 02:13.664
Down? What do you mean down?

02:13.698 --> 02:16.232
Down, on the floor,
unconscious.

02:16.267 --> 02:17.868
I called 9-1-1.

02:17.902 --> 02:19.169
The horses were
let out of their stalls,

02:19.203 --> 02:22.172
almost trampling each other
to get away.

02:22.206 --> 02:23.873
There must have been
a horse fight.

02:23.907 --> 02:25.708
Amy and Zeus are covered
with bites and cuts.

02:25.742 --> 02:27.277
You think she got caught
in the middle of it?

02:27.311 --> 02:28.778
Maybe. I don't know.

02:28.812 --> 02:30.213
I have no idea why
she was even there.

02:30.247 --> 02:32.648
She was there because
you texted her to be there.

02:32.683 --> 02:35.318
Texted her? I didn't.

02:35.353 --> 02:36.819
Yeah, you did.

02:36.854 --> 02:38.054
She said you needed help
with Amir -

02:38.089 --> 02:40.289
getting him calmed down
after the storm.

02:40.323 --> 02:44.794
No, I swear, I didn't
ask for her help.

02:46.730 --> 02:47.730
What's going on?

02:47.798 --> 02:49.231
Everything's gonna be okay.

02:49.299 --> 02:51.333
Can you, uh,
can you watch Katie for me?

02:51.368 --> 02:52.334
Um, yeah.

02:52.369 --> 02:53.636
Okay. Good girl.

02:53.670 --> 02:56.571
Breath sounds are clear
and equal bilaterally.

02:56.606 --> 02:59.408
Patient has spontaneous
respirations.

02:59.442 --> 03:01.877
GCs is five.

03:01.911 --> 03:06.148
<i>I want an mri done on her head</i>
<i>and neck immediately.</i>

03:06.182 --> 03:08.117
Caleb, I need you go
to the house

03:08.184 --> 03:10.419
and watch Katie and Georgie
for me.

03:10.487 --> 03:11.753
Yeah, okay.

03:14.423 --> 03:17.626
Uh, Amy's been hurt and-and
it sounds like it's serious.

03:17.660 --> 03:18.894
Are you kidding me?

03:18.928 --> 03:21.462
No. She's at the hospital and I
gotta go to her, so can you...

03:21.531 --> 03:22.731
Yeah, of course.

03:22.798 --> 03:24.566
<i>Okay.</i>

03:24.634 --> 03:26.034
Call me. I will.

03:26.068 --> 03:29.103
Excuse me, I'm, uh,
I'm Amy Fleming's father.

03:29.171 --> 03:30.471
Where is she?

03:30.506 --> 03:32.373
I'm afraid you'll have to wait
for the doctor, sir.

03:32.441 --> 03:35.910
Tim, we don't know
what happened yet.

03:35.944 --> 03:37.145
Well, I need to know
what happened.

03:37.212 --> 03:38.846
I need to see her.
Where is she?

03:38.914 --> 03:41.049
Oh, okay, just listen. Hi.

03:41.083 --> 03:44.885
I wonder if you have any
information, just anything at all?

03:44.953 --> 03:47.955
I'm sorry, her status is
unclear at this time.

03:48.023 --> 03:49.790
Unclear? Why?

03:49.858 --> 03:51.525
What happened to my daughter?

03:51.593 --> 03:52.793
I need to speak with someone
who knows something,

03:52.861 --> 03:54.394
<i>and I need to speak</i>
<i>to them now.</i>

03:54.462 --> 03:57.598
Excuse me, only
family members are allowed.

03:57.666 --> 04:00.601
If you're not a family member,
I have to ask you to leave.

04:00.669 --> 04:02.769
<i>Ridiculous!</i>

04:02.836 --> 04:05.872
Call me with any news.
Any at all.

04:08.443 --> 04:12.479
Dr. Berman, the
family's waiting.

04:14.415 --> 04:16.450
You okay? Hey. Yeah.

04:17.851 --> 04:19.151
Have you heard anything?

04:19.185 --> 04:20.920
No, nothing.

04:24.091 --> 04:25.725
You're Amy's family?

04:25.759 --> 04:27.060
Yes.

04:27.127 --> 04:30.663
Hello. Dr. Berman,
I'm the head of neurology here.

04:30.698 --> 04:34.266
All right then, Amy has suffered
a blow to the back of her head.

04:34.334 --> 04:38.104
Given the circumstances, it's probable
she's been kicked by a horse.

04:38.138 --> 04:39.805
She still hasn't
regained consciousness,

04:39.839 --> 04:42.208
which is quite normal
for a head injury of this type.

04:42.242 --> 04:44.910
When do you expect
she'll regain consciousness?

04:44.944 --> 04:46.878
<i>Well, that's
a bit unpredictable.</i>

04:46.913 --> 04:49.715
<i>Her vital signs are strong,</i> and
as far as motor response goes,

04:49.749 --> 04:53.251
she can move her arms and legs,
so there's no damage there.

04:53.285 --> 04:55.420
<i>But her eye response is slow.</i>

04:56.355 --> 04:57.723
Please, have a seat.

04:58.758 --> 05:02.160
Well, the blow was near
the occipital lobe of the brain,

05:02.194 --> 05:04.362
which contains
the vision center.

05:04.396 --> 05:07.099
At the present time,
Amy is not responding to light.

05:07.133 --> 05:09.200
What does that mean?

05:11.303 --> 05:13.605
I'm not the kind of doctor
who sugar-coats things.

05:13.639 --> 05:15.773
You need to know that
there is a possibility here

05:15.807 --> 05:18.876
of post-traumatic
cortical blindness.

05:18.910 --> 05:21.513
Now, this could very well
be a temporary state,

05:21.547 --> 05:23.414
but you must
also understand that

05:23.449 --> 05:27.051
if her sight does not return to
normal <i>in three to four days,</i>

05:27.085 --> 05:28.686
that there is
a sharply increased chance

05:28.720 --> 05:30.888
that there will be
lasting damage.

05:30.922 --> 05:33.223
<i>We will continue</i>
<i>to monitor Amy,</i>

05:33.258 --> 05:34.992
but we won't know much more
before morning.

05:35.027 --> 05:38.562
So my advice is to go home,
try to get some sleep.

05:38.596 --> 05:40.597
<i>I know it's hard.</i>

05:40.632 --> 05:41.931
You'll be called
when she regains consciousness

05:41.999 --> 05:45.135
or if there is
any sudden change.

05:45.170 --> 05:48.238
Thank you. Thank you.

05:51.276 --> 05:55.179
Well, I'm not leaving.
I've gotta go see her.

06:00.951 --> 06:05.254
Amy, come on,
you gotta wake up.

06:07.024 --> 06:09.325
You're going to be okay.

06:15.399 --> 06:19.602
Amy! Come on,
you gotta wake up, okay?

06:21.771 --> 06:23.806
I know you can do it.

06:27.811 --> 06:29.645
Come on.

06:32.448 --> 06:34.549
You can do this, Amy.

06:34.617 --> 06:36.318
Come on.

